    "section_text_tU7rc6": {
      "type": "section-text",
      "blocks": {
        "subheading_aQeNzt": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The 684 Collection</p>",
            "size": 100,
            "margin_bottom": 16
          }
        },
        "heading_RcBEX3": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The First Cut Initiated by Iron Heart Germany</p>",
            "size": 130,
            "heading_highlight_type": "italics",
            "highlight_color": "#d43747",
            "highlight_text_color": "#000000"
          }
        },
        "text_k3CFMA": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>When we started thinking about a new fit for Iron Heart Germany, it wasn’t about following a trend. It was about a feeling. We love Iron Heart for what it has always stood for: substance, weight, integrity. Fabrics with character. Denim that doesn’t try to please — it asks to be worn.<br/><br/>But we wanted space. Space to move. A silhouette that reflects how we wear denim today — without losing what makes Iron Heart what it is. That’s how the 684 was born.<br/><br/>The IH-684 marks a first for Iron Heart Germany. Developed in close collaboration with Haraki-San and the Iron Heart Japan team, the 684 is the first cut initiated by Iron Heart Germany to become part of the global Iron Heart lineup.<br/><br/>While the 684 will be integrated internationally in the future, the 16oz selvedge edition presented here remains exclusive to Iron Heart Germany.<br/><br/>This project reflects partnership, trust and a shared vision within the Iron Heart family.<br/><br/>No experiment,  <br/>but a permanent addition.</p>",
            "size": 100
          }
        }
      },
