    "text": {
      "type": "section-text",
      "blocks": {
        "subheading": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The 684 Denim</p>",
            "size": 100,
            "margin_bottom": 16
          }
        },
        "heading": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Exclusive 16oz Japanese Selvedge Denim</p>",
            "size": 130,
            "heading_highlight_type": "italics",
            "highlight_color": "#d43747",
            "highlight_text_color": "#000000"
          }
        },
        "text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>For this new silhouette, the fabric had to be right.<br/><br/>Haraki-san had just developed a new 16oz vintage-style selvedge denim, woven in Kojima at Takata Orimono on traditional shuttle looms. The fabric is made from Pima cotton ring-spun yarns, resulting in a textured, slightly irregular twill with depth and character.<br/><br/>Like Iron Heart’s 18oz vintage weave, this denim is designed to develop strong vertical tate-ochi fades over time. Because of the relaxed fit, the fades will appear more natural and subtle compared to tighter, heavier denim.<br/><br/>At 16oz, the fabric offers a rare balance: substantial enough for structure and durability, yet versatile enough for year-round wear.<br/><br/>While the 684 cut will be introduced in other fabrics in the future, this specific 16oz selvedge combination remains exclusive to Iron Heart Germany.</p>",
            "size": 100
          }
        },
