        "subheading": "The 684 Patch",
        "title": "<p>Tora. A Bridge/ Link between tradition and modernity</p>",
        "heading_highlight_type": "circle",
        "highlight_color": "#d43747",
        "highlight_text_color": "#000000",
        "heading_size": 130,
        "content": "<p>Animal motifs have long been part of Iron Heart’s patch tradition: Octopus. Snake. Duck.<br/><br/>For the 684, the idea was clear: a Japanese tiger. In Japanese culture, the Tora symbolizes courage, protection, and inner strength — values deeply aligned with Iron Heart itself.<br/><br/>The tiger was inspired by one of Maria’s tattoos and illustrated by Steve from Iron Heart International. The patch design was developed together with our long-time friend Carsten from Hamburg, founder of Agentur Mutter.<br/><br/>It is crafted from 14oz leather with a red print — a respectful nod to the classic Levi’s 501 patch design.<br/><br/>The number 684 follows naturally from the 634 foundation on which the cut is based. And it had to be even — for Maria, odd numbers were never an option.<br/><br/>Haraki-San approved. The 684 was born.<br/><br/>For this first edition, the tiger defines the identity of the cut.</p>",
        "text_alignment": "center",
        "button_text": "",
        "button_link": "",
        "button_color": "btn--black",
        "button_style": "btn--solid",
        "button_size": "btn--small",
